    {
      "id": "30b9a821fe76b695d36ee28a7480d890f6e68895",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-11-20 10:31:06.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+2\n\nStill trying to figure out the right mechanism to use this automatically...  would developers prefer a bit that automatically adds reviewers (this may result in 5+ reviewers for a patch which may or may not be totally relevant), or just dump the get_maintainers.pl output into a comment block during commit and/or add:\n\n Cc: Joe Maintainer <joe@example.com>\n\nTo the actual commit message?  Gerrit first do anything with \"Cc:\" today, but it would at least serve as a reminder of whom to assign it to.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "aa88ba3e6bde8aa6d4ca1010cff01687b04bfcaf",
      "author": {
