    {
      "id": "8f8964ae4772ca95d239da13fd87ce200c6984f8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2018-11-20 16:02:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nFailed optional test review-ldiskfs-arm on CentOS 7.0/aarch64, CentOS 7.0/x86_64 uploaded by Trevis Autotest2 from trevis-79vm23: https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/87c2f5d9-f367-49d3-b72e-3b285af62d70 ran 6 tests.  2 tests failed: lnet-selftest, sanity. %% THIS TEST SESSION CRASHED %%",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "a0bcf4c35c7a19004792dda3b7c835e02d836265",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2018-11-20 16:12:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nHm.  I'm not sure - I worry that adding it automatically to the commit message but not reviewers might confuse people who aren't experienced Gerrit users.  They'd assume those people had been cc'ed, I think.\n\nIf we don't want to always add the reviewers for anything touching those files (that seems best - it would get spammy for them, I think), then our goal is probably to make the information available to people easily...  Hmm.\n\nMaybe something in the commit notes, the text that appears when committing but does not go in the message?  I fear that would be ignored.  Sorry, I don't have a good answer here, unless we're OK with what the kernel does - Just make the info available if people need it.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "072ccc953d601a429b252a517daa627f75f535b6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 302,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "paf@cray.com",
        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2018-11-20 16:12:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nSorry, to clarify:\nWhat the kernel does, ie, nothing except provide file and script.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
